    <text type="letter">
        <body> 
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.01732_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1892-03-01">March 1, 1892</date>
                    <name type="place">Brooklyn, N.Y.<ptr target="loc.04954_n1"/></name>
                    <name type="place">185 Sterling Place,</name>
                </dateline>
                <salute>
                    Dear Cousin Walter,
                </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>As the Press gives us very frequent reports of your health &amp;c we have 
                refrained writing you. Knowing you would like to hear from us &amp; <choice><sic>reatives</sic><corr>relatives</corr></choice>
                we write you. Margaretta has had cough 4 or 5 weeks, some better now. I am not
                well, old bowel trouble. No relative here seriously ill. Have not heard from
                the Townsend<ptr target="loc.04954_n2"/> Tribe lately. We sincerely sympathise with you and with the 
                knowledge of your retention of <choice><sic>intelect</sic><corr>intellect</corr></choice>. 
                We join in our best Love to you, neither being able to meet you in person. 
            </p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Margaretta &amp; William A. Avery.</signed> 
            </closer>
